  "general_note": "Rabbits are prey animals and hide illness exceptionally well. Any change from normal behaviour should be taken seriously. A rabbit not eating for 12+ hours is a medical emergency. Rabbits cannot vomit, so toxin ingestion or GI issues can be especially serious.",
